Waking up proud.  Making good choices - choices for life.  Being encouraged and supported by friends and family.  A goal. A process.  Being in the moment, in the day.  Hope.  Love. We’ve got it cracking. 

Historic year and we’re not done!! 20 wins and Counting…. #NCAA  #NCAAW  #CCAA  #MarchMadness 

Ready for selection Sunday!!!

#MarchMadness You have to learn to love the grind.  Loving the grind and feeling fulfilled at the end of a hard day should be part of the culture that extreme talent embraces.  We are extreme talent and we’re responsible for our own success.  I’m South Central raised and my lingo and cadence allows me to navigate and avoid the, corn balls, weirdos and evil doers that this coaching profession houses.  I teach beyond self interest and my program has one rule - get better.  The choice has been simple, we’ve choose to get better every day and now we’re going dancing.  We’re action oriented, we’ve noticed each other, cared about each other, took a step back and sacrificed and it’s equaled success for our team.  Respectfully!! #WeAreLa #LosAngeles  #MarchMadness

Today, tomorrow, sometime this week- google “names of fallen service members”. Head to any of the links that come up and find just one name. Learn just one story.

Could be a name from WWI, WWII, the Global War on Terror, Civil War on PBS - or any conflict. 

And next weekend when you are hanging out and enjoying the freedoms we can sometimes take for granted, pass that name and story on to someone else.  I know you’ll be busy arguing about whose the GOAT - but this is simply a reminder to not take your life, liberties and pursuit of happiness for granted.  #TorinoKnows #TorinoTuesday #tuesday #lakers #heat #lebronjames #kobe #memorialday @nba @nbaonespn @nbaontnt
